      short updateValue(char key, short initialValueIfAbsent, ShortToShortFunction function)

    • asUnmodifiable

      MutableCharShortMap asUnmodifiable()
      Returns an unmodifiable view of this map, delegating all read-only operations to this map and throwing an UnsupportedOperationException for all mutating operations. This avoids the overhead of copying the map when calling CharShortMap.toImmutable() while still providing immutability.
      Returns:
      an unmodifiable view of this map

      short addToValue(char key, short toBeAdded)
      Increments and updates the value associated with the key, if a value exists, or sets the value to be the specified value if one does not.
      Parameters:
      key - the key
      toBeAdded - the amount to increment the existing value, if one exists, or to use as the initial value if one does not
